<h1>@HI{{ne}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @FORMATION{{@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}.}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}} is a sentence ending particle.
</p>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="feeling">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can indicate emotion or feelings of admiration.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kireina@KJ{{flower}}@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What a pretty flower.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="agreement">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can indicate agreement with the other person.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{book^hit}}nisoudesu@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That's so true.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="soften">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can soften a request.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{invariably}}zu@KJ{{hand^paper}}okudasai@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Be sure to write a letter to me.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="confirmation">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can request confirmation.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{meadow^rice*field}}san,@KJ{{now^day^come}}ruto@KJ{{say}}ttandesu@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Harada said he'd be coming today, right?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="opinion">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can indicate a mild assertion of opinion.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{soudesuka@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You think so?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="assertion">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can indicate a mild assertion.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{north^sea^road-way}}no@KJ{{direction}}ga@KJ{{cold}}ito@KJ{{think}}undesukedo@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I would think that Hokkaido is colder.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="yone">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can be used after <a href="grammar-particle-yo.html">@HI{{yo}}</a>.
The combination means "I assert this, but don't you agree?". This @HI{{@EM{{ne}}}} is pronounced with rising intonation.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{England^word}}:eigo}}ga@KJ{{part}}karuyo@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You understand English, don't you?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="kane">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can be used after <a href="grammar-particle-ka.html">@HI{{ka}}</a>.
The combination means "I'm not sure about this, am I right?". This @HI{{@EM{{ne}}}} is pronounced with falling intonation.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{before^life}}haii@KJ{{before^life}}desuka@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I doubt that he is a good teacher.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="middle">@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> can be in a non-sentence final position to draw the listener's attention or to confirm that
the listener has understood. This usage is typically found in telephone conversations.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{moshimoshi,@FG{{@KJ{{now^nightfall}}:konban'}}@EM{{ne}},@FG{{@KJ{{silver^sit}}:ginza}}de@KJ{{drink}}dekara@KJ{{homecoming}}rukara@EM{{ne}}
      @KJ{{ten^one^half^time^about*that*time}}ninaruyo.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Hello. Tonight I'll go to Ginza to drink, so I'll be home around 11:30.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="tene">@Vte{{}}@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}}</a> and @HI{{kara@EM{{ne}}}} are used to give a reason or cause for the speaker's feelings in an indirect and vague fashion.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{before^life}}hatotemokibishikute@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's because that teacher is very strict, you know?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{evening}}:yu}}beha@KJ{{drink}}misugitakara@EM{{ne}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's because I drank too much last night, you know?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ne}}}} can sometimes be pronounced @HI{{nee}}.
</p>

